        {
          "username": "Ilia Widman",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "103435280817976058046",
          "user_review_count": 6,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKWMoqIGPUDlIg04wWY1Kq0XnmYDBusG5vA6IFfLvlSf92irlKC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I\u2019m not sure why this place has such negative reviews- maybe there are multiple locations but the 17th st location has some of the most attentive providers I have experienced anywhere. I\u2019ve seen three doctors/NPs here in the last few years and all of them have sat down and spent concerted time with me- it has always felt thorough and never felt rushed. It seems like they really care about you here! They have also all responded promptly to any messages on MyChart. The other staff has always been really friendly too. I do recommend making an early morning appointment because it can get congested later in the day.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGNWIxbGlORmd6YkRWVlgzbEdNbUY1YVRkNFEzYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x9fd334e571b20b2!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkF5b1liNFgzbDVVX3lGMmF5aTd4Q3c%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-01-28T15:10:31+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Samantha",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "108201587975319533363",
          "user_review_count": 4,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ0ztQzB80tl_daVC27wT6ckSSB8cgvHq63T_gGd0TjSh76Tg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I am very dissatisfied with the overall service at this healthcare facility.Communication is major concern. It is extremely difficult to reach staff by phone, and there are frequent delays in receiving follow-ups for blood work and medical reports. Even when contacting customer service, I was told that this location is known for poor phone responsiveness.There are also persistent issues with administrative competence. The staff repeatedly fails to correctly handle insurance information and referrals, lack of proper training or attention to detail in this area.Especially , management appears to lack the experience and responsiveness needed to effectively resolve patient concerns or improve day-to-day operations.\n\nAlso, appointments with the doctor are consistently limited to around 15 minutes, which does not feel sufficient for proper patient care or for addressing concerns thoroughly.\n\nI will be transferring my care to another provider",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25odmFuTndZbm8yVlhBemVXNXNOMnBtUWxZeVRHYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x9fd334e571b20b2!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnhvanNwYno2VXAzeW5sN2pmQlYyTGc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "2 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-04-24T21:43:24+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Casey Ellis",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "100088008282620799017",
          "user_review_count": 7,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJh5uzUcQmxrcbmffZZDYmVo-UPNoP5gwp2AsE69gUk59qU1Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "When my mother passed away in 2022, I was in very bad shape.  At that time, I didn't have health insurance and a friend who had worked with the Institute for Family Health recommended I reach out to them.  The 17 St location in NYC was the branch nearest to me and they were just tremendously helpful, probably life-saving.  The psychiatrists (I saw three of them when going there), the nurses and the staff (in person and on the phone) were always kind and supportive, often going above and beyond in their assistance.  Things were often hectic there but I never felt rushed along and everyone made it clear they genuinely cared about their patients.  When cost was an issue, they proactively worked with me and it was clear I wasn't going to be abandoned if issues arose.  My employment situation has changed and I now have solid health insurance but I'll always be deeply grateful to everyone at the 17th St IFH.  If anyone from there reads this, thank you so very, very much!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2psTFEwOVRUM2g0TTBsT1VXMVBka2t4V1MweVdWRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x9fd334e571b20b2!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjlLQ09TT3h4M0lOUW1PdkkxWS0yWVE%7C%7C?hl=en",
